a-msdns-rfc5011keyrollovers.Description: An attribute that defines whether or not the DNS zone should be maintained using key rollover procedures defined in RFC 5011.

a-msdns-securedelegationpollingperiod.Description: An attribute that defines in seconds the time between polling attempts for child zone key rollovers.

a-msdns-signatureinceptionoffset.Description: An attribute that defines in seconds how far in the past DNSSEC signature validity periods should begin when signing the DNS zone.

a-msdns-signingkeydescriptors.Description: An attribute that contains the set of DNSSEC Signing Key Descriptors (SKDs) used by the DNS server to generate keys and sign the DNS zone.

a-msdns-signingkeys.Description: An attribute that contains the set of encrypted DNSSEC signing keys used by the DNS server to sign the DNS zone.

a-msdns-signwithnsec3.Description: An attribute used to define whether or not the DNS zone is signed with NSEC3.

a-msdrm-identitycertificate.Description: The XrML digital rights management certificates for this user.

a-msds-additionaldnshostname.Description: The attribute is used to store the additional DNS host name of a computer object. This attribute is used at the time a computer is renamed, or names are managed with "netdom computername".

a-msds-additionalsamaccountname.Description: This attribute is used to store the SAM account names that correspond to the DNS host names in ms-DS-Additional-Dns-Host-Name.

a-msds-alloweddnssuffixes.Description: The list of allowed suffixes for the dNSHostName attribute in computer objects.

a-msds-allowedtoactonbehalfofotheridenti.Description: This attribute is used for access checks to determine if a requestor has permission to act on the behalf of other identities to services running as this account.

a-msds-allowedtodelegateto.Description: This is an attribute on service account (computer or user account) objects. It contains a list of Service Principal Names (SPNs). This attribute is used to configure a service so that it can obtain service tickets that can be used for Constrained Delegation.

a-msds-alluserstrustquota.Description: Used to enforce a combined users quota on the total number of Trusted-Domain objects created by using the new control access right, Create-Inbound-Forest-Trust.

a-msds-appliestoresourcetypes.Description: For a resource property, this attribute indicates what resource types this resource property applies to.

a-msds-approx-immed-subordinates.Description: The value returned by this attribute is based on index sizes. This may be off by +/ 10% on large containers, and the error is theoretically unbounded, but using this attribute helps the UI display the contents of a container.

a-msds-authenticatedatdc.Description: Forward link for ms-DS-AuthenticatedTo-Accountlist. Identifies which DC a user has authenticated to.

a-msds-authenticatedtoaccountlist.Description: Backward link for ms-DS-AuthenticatedAt-DC. Identifies which users have authenticated to this Computer.

a-msds-auxiliary-classes.Description: This attribute lists the auxiliary classes that have been dynamically attached to an object. This attribute is not associated with a class. It is automatically populated by the system.

a-msds-azapplicationdata.Description: A string that is used by individual applications to store whatever information they may need to.

a-msds-azapplicationname.Description: A string that uniquely identifies an application object.

a-msds-azapplicationversion.Description: A version number to indicate that the AzApplication is updated.

a-msds-azbizrule.Description: Text of the script implementing the business rule.

a-msds-azbizrulelanguage.Description: The language that the business rule script is in (JScript, VBScript).

a-msds-azclassid.Description: A class ID required by the AzRoles UI on the AzApplication object.

a-msds-azdomaintimeout.Description: Time, in milliseconds, after a domain is detected to be unreachable and before the DC is tried again.

a-msds-azgenerateaudits.Description: A Boolean field that indicates whether runtime audits need to be turned on (include audits for access checks, and so on).

a-msds-azlastimportedbizrulepath.Description: The last imported business rule path.

a-msds-azldapquery.Description: A string that defines the LDAP query (max length 4096) which determines the membership of a user object to the group.

a-msds-azobjectguid.Description: The unique and portable identifier of AzMan objects

a-msds-azoperationid.Description: An application specific ID that makes the operation unique to the application.

a-msds-azscopename.Description: A string that uniquely identifies a scope object.

a-msds-azscriptenginecachemax.Description: The maximum number of scripts that are cached by the application.

a-msds-azscripttimeout.Description: The maximum time, in milliseconds, to wait for a script to finish auditing a specific policy.

a-msds-aztaskisroledefinition.Description: A Boolean field which indicates whether AzTask is a classic task or a role definition.

a-msds-behavior-version.Description: This attribute is used to track the domain or forest behavior version. It is a monotonically increasing number that is used to enable certain Active Directory features.

a-msds-bridgeheadserversused.Description: List of bridge head servers used by KCC in the previous run.

a-msds-bytearray.Description: An attribute for storing binary data.

a-msds-cached-membership.Description: The ms-DS-Cached-Membership attribute is used by the Security Accounts Manager for group expansion during token evaluation.

a-msds-cached-membership-time-stamp.Description: The ms-DS-Cached-Membership-Time-Stamp attribute is used by the Security Accounts Manager for group expansion during token evaluation.

a-msds-claimattributesource.Description: For a claim type object, this attribute points to the attribute that will be used as the source for the claim type.

a-msds-claimissinglevalued.Description: For a claim type object, this attribute identifies if the claim type or resource property can only contain single value.

a-msds-claimisvaluespacerestricted.Description: For a claim type, this attribute identifies whether a user can input values other than those described in the msDS-ClaimPossibleValues in applications.

a-msds-claimpossiblevalues.Description: For a claim type or resource property object, this attribute describes the values suggested to a user when the he/she use the claim type or resource property in applications.

a-msds-claimsharespossiblevalueswith.Description: For a resource property object, this attribute indicates that the suggested values of the claims issued are defined on the object that this linked attribute points to. Overrides ms-DS-Claim-Possible-Values on itself, if populated.

a-msds-claimsharespossiblevalueswithbl.Description: For a claim type object, this attribute indicates that the possible values described in ms-DS-Claim-Possible-Values are being referenced by other claim type objects.

a-msds-claimsource.Description: For a claim type, this attribute indicates the source of the claim type. For example, the source can be certificate.

a-msds-claimsourcetype.Description: For a security principal claim type, lists the type of store the issued claim is sourced from

a-msds-claimtypeappliestoclass.Description: For a claim type object, this linked attribute points to the AD security principal classes that for which claims should be issued. (For example, a link to the user class).

a-msds-claimvaluetype.Description: For a claim type object, specifies the value type of the claims issued.

a-msds-datetime.Description: An attribute for storing a date and time value.

a-msds-defaultquota.Description: The default quota that will apply to a security principal that creates an object in the NC if no quota specification exists that covers the security principal.

a-msds-disableforinstances.Description: The set of DSA objects, which represent ADAM instances, for which Service Connection Point publication should be disabled.

a-msds-disableforinstancesbl.Description: Backward link reference to the ms-DS-Service-Connection-Point-Publication-Service object.

a-msds-dnsrootalias.Description: Used to store the domain alias.

a-msds-egressclaimstransformationpolicy.Description: This is a link to a Claims Transformation Policy Object for the egress claims (claims leaving this forest) to the Trusted Domain. This is applicable only for an incoming or bidirectional Cross-Forest Trust. When this link is not present, all claims are allowed to egress as-is.

a-msds-enabledfeaturebl.Description: Scopes where this optional feature is enabled.

a-msds-entry-time-to-die.Description: Holds the absolute expiration time of a dynamic object in the directory.

a-msds-executescriptpassword.Description: Used during domain rename. This value cannot be written to or read from by using LDAP.

a-msds-externalkey.Description: A string that identifies an object in an external store, such as a record in a database.

a-msds-externalstore.Description: A string that identifies the location of an external store, such as a database.

a-msds-failedinteractivelogoncount.Description: The total number of failed interactive logons since this feature was turned on.

a-msds-failedinteractivelogoncountatlast.Description: The total number of failed interactive logons up until the last successful C-A-D logon.

a-msds-filtercontainers.Description: A multiple-valued string that contains the names of classes used to determine which container types should be shown by the Active Directory Users and Computers snap-in when filtering.

a-msds-generationid.Description: For virtual machine snapshot resuming detection. This attribute represents the VM Generation ID.

a-msds-geocoordinatesaltitude.Description: Geo-coordinates for location services, specifically altitude (in millimeters) of the office or conference room.

a-msds-geocoordinateslatitude.Description: Geo-coordinates for location services, specifically, latitude (in microdegrees) of the office or conference room.

a-msds-geocoordinateslongitude.Description: Geo-coordinates for location services, specifically, longitude (in microdegrees) of the office or conference room.

a-msds-groupmsamembership.Description: This attribute is used for access checks to determine if a requestor has permission to retrieve the password for a group MSA.

a-msds-habseniorityindex.Description: Contains the seniority index as applied by the organization where the person works.

a-msds-hasdomainncs.Description: Directory service replication information that details the domain naming contexts present on a particular server.

a-msds-hasfullreplicancs.Description: Identifies the partitions held as full replicas.

a-msds-hasinstantiatedncs.Description: DS replication state information, analogous to (and a superset of) the existing attributes hasMasterNCs and hasPartialReplicaNCs. To be used by the KCC when setting up replication partners.

a-msds-hasmasterncs.Description: Contains the naming contexts held by a domain controller. This attribute deprecates has-Master-NCs.

a-msds-hostserviceaccount.Description: Service Accounts configured to run on this computer.

a-msds-ingressclaimstransformationpolicy.Description: This is a link to a Claims Transformation Policy Object for the ingress claims (claims entering this forest) from the Trusted Domain. This is applicable only for an outgoing or bidirectional Cross-Forest Trust. If this link is absent, all the ingress claims are dropped.

a-msds-integer.Description: An attribute for storing an integer.

a-msds-intid.Description: The ms-DS-IntId attribute is for internal use only.

a-msds-isfullreplicafor.Description: Backward link for ms-DS-Has-Domain-NCs. Identifies which DCs hold that partition as their primary domain.

a-msds-isgc.Description: Identifies the state of the Global Catalog on the DC.

a-msds-ispartialreplicafor.Description: Backward link for hasPartialReplicaNCs. Identifies which DCs hold that partition as a partial replica.

a-msds-ispossiblevaluespresent.Description: This attribute identifies if ms-DS-Claim-Possible-Values on linked resource property must have value or must not have value.

a-msds-isrodc.Description: Shows whether a DC is an RODC.

a-msds-isusedasresourcesecurityattribute.Description: For a resource property, this attribute indicates whether it is being used as a secure attribute.

a-msds-isusercachableatrodc.Description: For a Read-Only Domain Controller (RODC), identifies whether the specified user's secrets can be cached.

a-msds-keyversionnumber.Description: The Kerberos version number of the current key for this account. This is a constructed attribute.

a-msds-krbtgtlink.Description: Used with RODCs to define which krbtgt_XXXX account corresponds to each RODC.

a-msds-krbtgtlinkbl.Description: Backward link for the ms-DS-KrbTgt-Link attribute.

a-msds-lastfailedinteractivelogontime.Description: The time that an incorrect password was presented during a Ctrl+Alt+Delete logon.

a-msds-lastknownrdn.Description: Contains the original RDN of a deleted object.

a-msds-lastsuccessfulinteractivelogontim.Description: The time that the correct password was presented during a Ctrl+Alt+Delete logon.

a-msds-localeffectivedeletiontime.Description: Deletion time of the object in the local DIT.

a-msds-localeffectiverecycletime.Description: Recycle time of the object in the local DIT.

a-msds-lockoutduration.Description: Lockout duration for locked out user accounts.

a-msds-lockoutobservationwindow.Description: The period of time that a user account will be locked out.

a-msds-lockoutthreshold.Description: Lockout threshold for the lock out of user accounts.

a-msds-logontimesyncinterval.Description: This attribute controls the granularity, in days, with which the last logon time for a user or computer, recorded in the lastLogonTimestamp attribute, is replicated to all DCs in a domain.

a-msds-managedpassword.Description: This constructed attribute returns a blob that contains the clear-text previous and current password, TimeUntilEpochExpires, and TimeUntilNextScheduledUpdate for a group MSA.

a-msds-managedpasswordid.Description: This attribute contains the key identifier for the current managed password data for a group MSA.

a-msds-managedpasswordinterval.Description: This attribute is used to retrieve the number of days before a managed password is automatically changed for a group MSA.

a-msds-managedpasswordpreviousid.Description: This constructed attribute contains the key identifier for the previous managed password data for a group MSA.

a-msds-maximumpasswordage.Description: Maximum age for user account passwords.

a-msds-membersforazrole.Description: List of member application groups or users linked to Az-Role.

a-msds-membersforazrolebl.Description: Backward link from member application group or user to Az-Role objects linking to it.

a-msds-membersofresourcepropertylist.Description: For a resource property list object, this multi-valued link attribute points to one or more resource property objects.

a-msds-membersofresourcepropertylistbl.Description: Backlink for ms-DS-Members-Of-Resource-Property-List. For a resource property object, this attribute references the resource property list object that it is a member of.

a-msds-minimumpasswordage.Description: Minimum age for user account passwords.

a-msds-minimumpasswordlength.Description: Minimum length for user account passwords.

a-msds-nc-replica-locations.Description: A list of servers that are the replica set for the corresponding Non-Domain Naming Context.

a-msds-nc-ro-replica-locations.Description: A linked attribute on a cross reference object for a partition. Lists the DC that should host the partition in a read-only manner.

a-msds-ncreplcursors.Description: A list of past and present replication partners, and how current we are with each of them.

a-msds-ncreplinboundneighbors.Description: Replication partners for this partition. This server obtains replication data from these other servers, which act as sources.

a-msds-nctype.Description: A bitfield that maintains information about aspects of an NC replica that is relevant to replication.

a-msds-neverrevealgroup.Description: Used with RODCs to define which users, computers, and groups are not allowed to have their passwords cached on an RODC.

a-msds-non-security-group-extra-classes.Description: The common names of the nonstandard classes that can be added to a nonsecurity group through the Active Directory Users and Computers snap-in.

a-msds-nonmembers.Description: This attribute serves the same purpose as the Non-Security-Member attribute but with scoping rules applied.

a-msds-nonmembersbl.Description: Backward link from non-member group or user to Az groups that link to it (same functionality as Non-Security-Member-BL).

a-msds-objectreference.Description: A link to the object that uses the data stored in the object that contains this attribute.

a-msds-oidtogrouplink.Description: For an OID, identifies the group object that corresponds to the issuance policy represented by this OID.

a-msds-oidtogrouplinkbl.Description: Backward link for ms-DS-OIDToGroup-Link. Identifies the issuance policy, represented by an OID object, that is mapped to this group.

a-msds-operationsforazrole.Description: List of operations linked to Az-Role.

a-msds-operationsforazrolebl.Description: Backward link from Az-Operation to Az-Role objects that link to it.

a-msds-operationsforaztask.Description: List of operations linked to Az-Task.

a-msds-operationsforaztaskbl.Description: Backward link from Az-Operation to Az-Task objects that link to it.

a-msds-optionalfeatureflags.Description: An integer value that contains flags that define behavior of an optional feature in Active Directory.

a-msds-other-settings.Description: This multiple-valued attribute is used to store any configurable setting for the DS stored in the NAME=VALUE format.

a-msds-passwordcomplexityenabled.Description: Password complexity status for user accounts.

a-msds-passwordhistorylength.Description: Password history length for user accounts.

a-msds-passwordreversibleencryptionenabl.Description: Password-reversible encryption status for user accounts.

a-msds-perusertrustquota.Description: Used to enforce a per-user quota for creating Trusted-Domain objects that are authorized by the new control access right, Create-Inbound-Forest-Trust. This attribute limits the number of Trusted-Domain objects that can be created by a single non-admin user.

a-msds-perusertrusttombstonesquota.Description: Used to enforce a per-user quota for deleting Trusted-Domain objects when authorization is based on matching the user's SID.

a-msds-phoneticcompanyname.Description: Contains the phonetic company name where the person works.

a-msds-phoneticdepartment.Description: Contains the phonetic department name where the person works.

a-msds-phoneticdisplayname.Description: The phonetic display name of an object. In the absence of a phonetic display name, the existing display name is used.

a-msds-phoneticfirstname.Description: Contains the phonetic given name or first name of the person.

a-msds-phoneticlastname.Description: Contains the phonetic last name of the person.

a-msds-portldap.Description: Specifies which port is used by the directory service to listen for LDAP requests.

a-msds-portssl.Description: Specifies which port is used by the directory service for SSL requests.

a-msds-preferred-gc-site.Description: The ms-DS-Preferred-GC-Site attribute is used by the Security Accounts Manager for group expansion during token evaluation.

a-msds-primarycomputer.Description: For a user or group object, identifies the primary computers.

a-msds-principalname.Description: Account name for the security principal (constructed).

a-msds-promotionsettings.Description: For a computer, contains an XML string to be used for delegated DSA promotion.

a-msds-psoappliesto.Description: Links to objects that this password settings object applies to.

a-msds-quotaamount.Description: The assigned quota in terms of number of objects owned in the database.

a-msds-replication-notify-first-dsa-dela.Description: This attribute controls the delay in time between changes to the DS, and notification of the first replica partner for an NC.

a-msds-replication-notify-subsequent-dsa.Description: This attribute controls the delay in time between notification of each subsequent replica partner for an NC.

a-msds-replicationepoch.Description: This is used to hold the epoch under which all the DCs are replicating. An epoch is the period of time in which a domain has a specific name. A new epoch starts when a domain name change occurs.

a-msds-replvaluemetadata.Description: A list of metadata for each value of an attribute. The metadata indicates who changed the value last.

a-msds-requireddomainbehaviorversion.Description: Required domain function level for this feature.

a-msds-requiredforestbehaviorversion.Description: Required forest function level for this feature.

a-msds-retiredreplncsignatures.Description: Information about naming contexts that are no longer held on this computer.

a-msds-revealedusers.Description: Used with RODCs to identify the user objects whose secrets have been disclosed to that RODC.

a-msds-revealondemandgroup.Description: Used with RODCs to define which users, computers, and groups are allowed to have their passwords cached on an RODC.

a-msds-secondarykrbtgtnumber.Description: Identifies the protocol identification number associated with the secondary domain.

a-msds-security-group-extra-classes.Description: The common names of the nonstandard classes that can be added to a security group through the Active Directory Users and Computers snap-in.

a-msds-seniorityindex.Description: Contains the seniority index as applied by the organization where the person works.

a-msds-serviceaccount.Description: The FPO that represents the ADAM service account.

a-msds-serviceaccountbl.Description: Backward link reference to the AD/AM DSA object that uses this service account.

a-msds-serviceaccountdnsdomain.Description: ADAM: The domain which the ADAM service account is a member of.

a-msds-settings.Description: Used to store settings for an object. Its use is solely determined by the object's owner. We recommend using it to store name/value pairs. For example, color=blue.

a-msds-site-affinity.Description: The ms-DS-Site-Affinity attribute is used by the Security Accounts Manager for group expansion during token evaluation.

a-msds-sitename.Description: Lists the site name that corresponds to the DC.

a-msds-sourceobjectdn.Description: Contains the string representation of the distinguished name of the object in another forest that corresponds to this object.

a-msds-spnsuffixes.Description: This attribute describes the suffixes of DNS host names used by servers in the forest. These DNS suffixes will be shared with other forests that have cross-forest trust with this forest.

a-msds-supportedencryptiontypes.Description: The encryption algorithms supported by user, computer or trust accounts.

a-msds-tasksforazrolebl.Description: Backward link from Az-Task to Az-Role objects that link to it.

a-msds-tasksforaztaskbl.Description: Backward link from Az-Task to the Az-Task objects that link to it.

a-msds-topquotausage.Description: The list of top quota users currently in the directory database, ordered by decreasing quota usage.

a-msds-transformationrules.Description: Specifies the Transformation Rules for Cross-Forest Claims Transformation.

a-msds-updatescript.Description: This is used to hold the script with the domain restructure instructions.

a-msds-userpasswordexpired.Description: Indicates whether the password for the account that this attribute references has expired. True if the password has expired; otherwise, False.

a-msds-userpasswordexpirytimecomputed.Description: Contains the expiry time for the user's current password.

a-msds-usnlastsyncsuccess.Description: The USN at which the last successful replication synchronization occurred.

a-msds-valuetypereference.Description: This attribute is used to link a resource property object to its value type.

a-msds-valuetypereferencebl.Description: This is the back link for ms-DS-Value-Type-Reference. It links a value type object back to resource properties.

a-mssfu30keyvalues.Description: Contains internal data that the NIS server uses to store temporary data.

a-mssfu30ypservers.Description: Contains a list of NIS servers in an NIS domain.

a-mstapi-conferenceblob.Description: A binary BLOB of data that describes various properties of a TAPI multicast conference. Its format and content are determined by the value of the attribute Protocol-Id in the same object. Typically, the data in this BLOB conforms to RFC2327.

a-mstapi-protocolid.Description: This attribute indicates the TAPI conference type. This attribute is used to determine how the binary BLOB in the ms-TAPI-Conference-Blob attribute is to be interpreted. This attribute is an arbitrary string, typically less than 100 characters in length.

a-mstapi-uid.Description: Provides the name of a TAPI multicast conference. It is the naming attribute of the Rt-Conference class.

a-mstpm-ownerinformation.Description: Contains the owner information of a particular TPM.

a-mstpm-ownerinformationtemp.Description: This attribute contains temporary owner information for a particular TPM.

a-mstpm-srkpubthumbprint.Description: This attribute contains the thumbprint of the SrkPub corresponding to a particular TPM. This helps to index the TPM devices in the directory.

a-mstpm-tpminformationforcomputer.Description: This attribute links a Computer object to a TPM object.

a-mstpm-tpminformationforcomputerbl.Description: This attribute links a TPM object to the Computer objects associated with it.

a-mstsallowlogon.Description: Specifies whether the user is allowed to log on to the Terminal Server. The value is 1 if logon is allowed, and 0 if logon is not allowed.

a-mstsbrokenconnectionaction.Description: Terminal Services session Broken Connection Action specifies the action to take when a Terminal Services session limit is reached.

a-mstsconnectclientdrives.Description: Terminal Services session Connect Client Drives specifies whether to reconnect to mapped client drives at logon.

a-mstsconnectprinterdrives.Description: Terminal Services session Connect Printer Drives specifies whether to reconnect to mapped client printers at logon.

a-mstsdefaulttomainprinter.Description: Terminal Services Default To Main Printer specifies whether to print automatically to the client's default printer.

a-mstsendpointdata.Description: This attribute represents the VM Name for a computer in a TSV deployment.

a-mstsendpointplugin.Description: This attribute represents the name of the plug-in that handles the orchestration.

a-mstsendpointtype.Description: This attribute defines whether the computer is a physical computer or a virtual machine.

a-mstsexpiredate2.Description: Expiration date of the second TS per user CAL.

a-mstsexpiredate3.Description: Expiration date of the third TS per user CAL.

a-mstsexpiredate4.Description: Expiration date of the fourth TS per user CAL.

a-mstshomedirectory.Description: Terminal Services Home Directory specifies the Home directory for the user.

a-mstshomedrive.Description: Terminal Services Home Drive specifies a Home drive for the user.

a-mstsinitialprogram.Description: Terminal Services Session Initial Program specifies the path and file name of the application that the user wants to start automatically when the user logs on to the Terminal Server.

a-mstslicenseversion2.Description: Version of the second terminal server per user CAL.

a-mstslicenseversion3.Description: Version of the third terminal server per user CAL.

a-mstslicenseversion4.Description: Version of the fourth terminal server per user CAL.

a-mstsmanagingls2.Description: Issuer name of the second terminal server per user CAL.

a-mstsmanagingls3.Description: Issuer name of the third terminal server per user CAL.

a-mstsmanagingls4.Description: Issuer name of the fourth terminal server per user CAL.

a-mstsmaxdisconnectiontime.Description: Terminal Services session Maximum Disconnection Time is the maximum amount of time, in minutes, that a disconnected Terminal Services session remains active on the terminal server.

a-mstsmaxidletime.Description: Terminal Services session Maximum Idle Time is the maximum amount of time, in minutes, that the Terminal Services session can remain idle.

a-mstsprimarydesktop.Description: This attribute represents the forward link to a user's primary desktop.

a-mstsprimarydesktopbl.Description: This attribute represents the backward link to a user.

a-mstsprofilepath.Description: Terminal Services Profile Path specifies a roaming or mandatory profile path to use when the user logs on to the terminal server. The profile path is in the following network path format: **\\ServerName\ProfilesFolderName\**UserName.

a-mstsreconnectionaction.Description: Terminal Services session Reconnection Action specifies whether to allow reconnection to a disconnected Terminal Services session from any client computer.

a-mstsremotecontrol.Description: Terminal Services Remote Control specifies whether to allow remote observation or remote control of the user's Terminal Services session.

a-mstssecondarydesktopbl.Description: This attribute represents the backward link to a user.

a-mstssecondarydesktops.Description: This attribute represents the array of forward links to a user's secondary desktops.

a-mstsworkdirectory.Description: Terminal Services session Work Directory specifies the working directory path for the user.

a-parentcacertificatechain.Description: DER-encoded X.509v3 certificate for the parent certification authority.

a-parentguid.Description: This is a constructed attribute, invented to support the DirSync control. This attribute holds the objectGuid of an object's parent when replicating an object's creation, rename, or move.

a-partialattributedeletionlist.Description: Tracks the internal replication state of partial replicas (that is, on GCs). Attribute of the partial replica NC object. Used when the GC is in the process of removing attributes from the objects in its partial replica NCs.

a-partialattributeset.Description: Tracks the internal replication state of partial replicas (that is, on GCs). Attribute of the partial replica NC object. Defines the set of attributes present on a particular partial replica NC.

a-pendingcacertificates.Description: The certificates that are about to become effective for this certification authority.

a-pendingparentca.Description: Reference to the certification authorities that issued the pending certificates for this certification authority.

a-permsgdialogdisplaytable.Description: The Per Message options MAPI display table.

a-perrecipdialogdisplaytable.Description: The Per Recipient options MAPI display table.

a-photo.Description: An object encoded in G3 fax as explained in recommendation T.4, with an ASN.1 wrapper to make it compatible with an X.400 BodyPart as defined in X.420.

a-physicaldeliveryofficename.Description: Contains the office location in the user's place of business.

a-physicallocationobject.Description: Used to map a device (for example, a printer, computer, and so on) to a physical location.

a-pkicriticalextensions.Description: The list of critical extensions in the certificate template.

a-pkidefaultcsps.Description: The list of cryptographic service providers for the certificate template.

a-pkidefaultkeyspec.Description: The private key specification for the certificate template.

a-pkienrollmentaccess.Description: The PKI-Enrollment-Access attribute is for internal use only.

a-pkiexpirationperiod.Description: The validity period for the certificate template.

a-pkiextendedkeyusage.Description: The enhanced key usage OIDs for the certificate template.

a-pkikeyusage.Description: The key usage extension for the certificate template.

a-pkimaxissuingdepth.Description: The maximum length of the certificate chain issued by the certificate.

a-pkioverlapperiod.Description: The period by when the certificate should be renewed before it is expired.

a-pkt.Description: DFS Partition Knowledge Table. Describes the structure of a Distributed File System hierarchy.

a-pktguid.Description: Unique ID of a given Distributed File System Partition Knowledge Table.

a-policyreplicationflags.Description: Determines which LSA properties are replicated to clients.

a-portname.Description: List of port names. For example, for printer ports or comm ports.

a-possibleinferiors.Description: The list of objects that this object can contain.

a-posssuperiors.Description: The list of objects that can contain this class.

a-postaladdress.Description: The mailing address for the object.

a-postalcode.Description: The postal or zip code for mail delivery.

a-postofficebox.Description: The post office box number for this object.

a-preferreddeliverymethod.Description: The X.500-preferred way to deliver to addressee.

a-preferredlanguage.Description: The preferred written or spoken language for a person.

a-preferredou.Description: The Organizational Unit to show by default on user' s desktop.

a-prefixmap.Description: The Prefix-Map attribute is for internal use only.

a-presentationaddress.Description: Specifies a presentation address associated with an object that represents an OSI application entity.

a-previouscacertificates.Description: Last expired certificate for this certification authority.

a-previousparentca.Description: Reference to the certification authorities that issued the last expired certificate for a certification authority.

a-primarygroupid.Description: Contains the relative identifier (RID) for the primary group of the user. By default, this is the RID for the Domain Users group.

a-primarygrouptoken.Description: A computed attribute that is used in retrieving the membership list of a group, such as Domain Users. The complete membership of such groups is not stored explicitly for scaling reasons.

a-printbinnames.Description: A list of printer bin names.

a-printcollate.Description: TRUE if a printer has collating bins.

a-printcolor.Description: TRUE if a printer can print in color.

a-printduplexsupported.Description: Indicates the type of duplex support a printer has.

a-printendtime.Description: The time a print queue stops servicing jobs.

a-printername.Description: The display name of an attached printer.

a-printformname.Description: The name of the currently loaded form.

a-printkeepprintedjobs.Description: TRUE if printed jobs are kept.

a-printlanguage.Description: The supported page description language (for example, PostScript, PCL).

a-printmaxcopies.Description: The maximum number of copies a device can print.

a-printmediaready.Description: A list of available media for a printer.

a-printmediasupported.Description: A list of media supported by a printer.

a-printmemory.Description: The amount of memory installed in a printer.

a-printnotify.Description: A user-supplied string that specifies the notification contact.

a-printnumberup.Description: The number of page images per sheet.

a-printorientationssupported.Description: The page rotation for landscape printing.

a-printpagesperminute.Description: Driver-supplied print rate in pages per minute.

a-printseparatorfile.Description: The file path of the printer separator page.

a-printspooling.Description: A string that represents the type of printer spooling.

a-printstaplingsupported.Description: TRUE if the printer supports stapling. Supplied by the driver.

a-printstarttime.Description: The time a print queue begins servicing jobs.

a-printstatus.Description: Status from the print spooler. Currently unused.

a-priority.Description: The current priority (of a process, print job, and so on).

a-priorsettime.Description: The previous time set for a secret.

a-priorvalue.Description: The previous value for a secret.

a-privilegedisplayname.Description: Display name for a WindowsÂ NT privilege.

a-privilegeholder.Description: List of Distinguished Names of principals granted this privilege.

a-privilegevalue.Description: A value that represents an WindowsÂ NT privilege.

a-productcode.Description: This attribute contains a unique identifier for an application for a particular product release, represented as a string GUID, for example "{12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012}". Letters used in this GUID must be uppercase. This ID must vary for different versions and languages.

a-profilepath.Description: Specifies a path to the user's profile. This value can be a null string, a local absolute path, or a UNC path.

a-proxiedobjectname.Description: This attribute is used internally by Active Directory to help track interdomain moves.

a-proxyaddresses.Description: A proxy address is the address by which a Microsoft Exchange Server recipient object is recognized in a foreign mail system. Proxy addresses are required for all recipient objects, such as custom recipients and distribution lists.

a-proxygenerationenabled.Description: TRUE if proxy generation is enabled.

a-proxylifetime.Description: Contains the lifetime for a proxy object.

a-publickeypolicy.Description: Reference to the Public Key policy for this domain.

a-purportedsearch.Description: The search argument for an address book view.

a-pwdhistorylength.Description: The number of old passwords to save.

a-pwdlastset.Description: The date and time that the password for this account was last changed. This value is stored as a large integer that represents the number of 100 nanosecond intervals since January 1, 1601 (UTC). If this value is set to 0 and the User-Account-Control attribute does not contain the UF_DONT_EXPIRE_PASSWD flag, then the user must set the password at the next logon.

a-pwdproperties.Description: Password Properties. Part of Domain Policy. A bitfield to indicate complexity and storage restrictions.

a-qualityofservice.Description: Local or domain quality of service bits on policy objects.

a-querypoint.Description: The URL or UNC of a query page or other front end for accessing a catalog.

a-querypolicybl.Description: List of all objects holding references to a given Query-Policy.

a-querypolicyobject.Description: Reference to the default Query-Policy in force for this server.

a-rangelower.Description: The minimum value or length of an attribute.

a-rangeupper.Description: The maximum value or length of an attribute.

a-rdnattid.Description: The RDN for the attribute that is used to name a class.

a-registeredaddress.Description: Specifies a mnemonic for an address associated with an object at a particular city location. The mnemonic is registered in the country/region in which the city is located and is used in the provision of the Public Telegram Service.

a-remoteservername.Description: Used wherever one or more computer names must be stored.

a-remotesourcetype.Description: Type of pointer to foreign object.

a-remotestorageguid.Description: This attribute contains the GUID for a remote storage object.

a-replicasource.Description: This attribute contains the GUID of a replication source.

a-replinterval.Description: The attribute of Site-Link objects that defines the interval, in minutes, between replication cycles between the sites in the Site-List. Must be a multiple of 15 minutes (the granularity of cross-site DS replication), a minimum of 15 minutes, and a maximum of 10,080 minutes (one week).

a-replpropertymetadata.Description: Tracks internal replication state information for DS objects. Information here can be extracted in public form through the public API DsReplicaGetInfo(). Present on all DS objects.

a-repltopologystayofexecution.Description: The delay between deleting a server object and it being permanently removed from the replication topology.

a-repluptodatevector.Description: Tracks internal replication state information for an entire NC. Information here can be extracted in public form through the API DsReplicaGetInfo(). Present on all NC root objects.

a-repsfrom.Description: Lists the servers from which the directory will accept changes for the defined naming context.

a-repsto.Description: Lists the servers that the directory will notify of changes and servers to which the directory will send changes on Request for the defined naming context.

a-requiredcategories.Description: This attribute contains a list of component category IDs an object (such as an application) requires to run.

a-retiredrepldsasignatures.Description: Tracks the past DS replication identities of a given DC.

a-revision.Description: The revision level for a security descriptor or other change. Only used in the sam-server and ds-ui-settings objects.

a-rid.Description: The relative Identifier of an object.

a-ridallocationpool.Description: A pool that was prefetched for use by the RID manager when the RID-Previous-Allocation-Pool has been used up.

a-ridavailablepool.Description: The space from which RID Pools are allocated.

a-ridmanagerreference.Description: The Distinguished Name for the RID Manager of an object.

a-ridnextrid.Description: The next free Relative Identifier in the current pool.

a-ridpreviousallocationpool.Description: The RID-Previous-Allocation-Pool attribute contains the pool of relative identifiers (RIDs) that a domain controller allocates from. This attribute is an eight-byte value that contains a pair of four-byte integers that represent the start and end values of the RID pool. The start value is in the lower four bytes and the end value is in the upper four bytes.

a-ridsetreferences.Description: List of references to RID-Set objects that manage Relative Identifier (RID) allocation.

a-ridusedpool.Description: The RID Pools that have been used by a DC.

a-rightsguid.Description: The GUID used to represent an extended right within an access control entry.

a-roleoccupant.Description: The distinguished name of an object that fulfills an organizational role.

a-roomnumber.Description: The room number of an object.

a-roottrust.Description: The Distinguished Name of another Cross-Ref.

a-rpcnsannotation.Description: A string that describs a given RPC Profile element.

a-rpcnsbindings.Description: The list of RPC bindings for the current interface.

a-rpcnscodeset.Description: The list of character sets supported by the server.

a-rpcnsentryflags.Description: Flag to indicate that the RPC NS entry was explicitly created.

a-rpcnsgroup.Description: A reference to an RPC Server entry or another RPC Group.

a-rpcnsinterfaceid.Description: An Interface ID supported by a given server.

a-rpcnsobjectid.Description: The Object IDs exported by a given server.

a-rpcnspriority.Description: The priority of a given RPC profile entry.

a-rpcnsprofileentry.Description: The list of entries for the current priority.

a-rpcnstransfersyntax.Description: The UUID of the transfer syntax supported by the current entry.

a-samaccountname.Description: The logon name used to support clients and servers running earlier versions of the operating system, such as Windows NT 4.0, Windows 95, Windows 98, and LAN Manager.

a-samaccounttype.Description: This attribute contains information about every account type object. You can enumerate a list of account types or you can use the Display Information API to create a list. Because computers, normal user accounts, and trust accounts can also be enumerated as user objects, the values for these accounts must be a contiguous range.

a-samdomainupdates.Description: Contains a bitmask of performed SAM operations on Active Directory.

a-schedule.Description: A schedule BLOB as defined by the Windows NT Job Service. Used by replication.

a-schemaflagsex.Description: The Schema-Flags-Ex attribute is not currently used.

a-schemaidguid.Description: The unique identifier for an attribute.

a-schemainfo.Description: An internal binary value used to detect schema changes between DCs and force a schema NC replication cycle before replicating any other NC. Used to resolve ties when the schema FSMO is seized and a change is made on more than one DC.

a-schemaupdate.Description: The Schema-Update attribute is not currently used.

a-schemaversion.Description: The version number for the schema.

a-scopeflags.Description: The Scope-Flags attribute is not currently used.

a-scriptpath.Description: This attribute specifies the path for the user's logon script. The string can be null.

a-sdrightseffective.Description: This constructed attribute returns a single DWORD value that can have up to three bits set:

a-searchflags.Description: Contains a set of flags that specify search and indexing information for an attribute. See Remarks.

a-searchguide.Description: Specifies information of suggested search criteria, which may be included in some entries that are expected to be a convenient base-object for the search operation, for example, country/region or organization.

a-secretary.Description: Contains the distinguished name of the secretary for an account.

a-securityidentifier.Description: A unique value of variable length used to identify a user account, group account, or logon session to which an ACE applies.

a-seealso.Description: List of distinguished names that are related to an object.

a-seqnotification.Description: This attribute contains a counter that is incremented daily. This counter value is given to the link tracking service which adds the value to its volumes and link source files when they are refreshed. The domain controller maintains this value.

a-serialnumber.Description: Part of X.500 specification. Not used by Active Directory.

a-serverreference.Description: Found in a site computer object. Contains the distinguished name of the domain controller in the domain naming context.

a-serverreferencebl.Description: Found in the domain naming context. The distinguished name of a computer under the sites folder.

a-serverrole.Description: For compatibility with pre-Windows 2000 Server servers. A computer running Windows NT Server can be a standalone server, a primary domain controller (PDC), or a backup domain controller (BDC).

a-serverstate.Description: Indicates whether the server is enabled or disabled. A value of 1 indicates that the server is enabled. A value of 2 indicates that the server is disabled. All other values are invalid.

a-servicebindinginformation.Description: Service-specific binding information in string format.

a-serviceclassid.Description: The GUID for the Service class.

a-serviceclassname.Description: The string name of the service that an administration point represents.

a-servicednsname.Description: The DNS name to look up to find a server running this service.

a-servicednsnametype.Description: Type of DNS Record to look up for this service. For example, A or SRV.

a-serviceprincipalname.Description: List of principal names used for mutual authentication with an instance of a service on this computer.

a-setupcommand.Description: This attribute indicates whether a setup command is required to set up this application.

a-shadowexpire.Description: Contains the absolute date to expire the account.

a-shadowflag.Description: Contains the section of the shadow map that is used to store the flag value.

a-shadowinactive.Description: Contains the number of days of inactivity that is allowed for the user.

a-shadowlastchange.Description: Contains the last change of the shadow information.

a-shadowmax.Description: Contains the maximum number of days a password can be valid.

a-shadowmin.Description: Contains the minimum number of days between shadow changes.

a-shadowwarning.Description: Contains the number of days before the password expires to warn the user.

a-shellcontextmenu.Description: The order number and GUID of the context menu for this object.

a-shellpropertypages.Description: The order number and GUID of property pages for managing Active Directory objects. These property pages can be accessed from the Windows shell. For more information see the document, Extending the User Interface for Directory Objects.

a-shortservername.Description: Pre-Windows 2000 compatible server name for print servers.

a-showinaddressbook.Description: This attribute is used to indicate in which MAPI address books an object will appear. It is usually maintained by the Exchange Recipient Update Service.

a-showinadvancedviewonly.Description: TRUE if this attribute is to be visible in the Advanced mode of the UI.

a-sidhistory.Description: Contains previous SIDs used for the object if the object was moved from another domain. Whenever an object is moved from one domain to another, a new SID is created and that new SID becomes the objectSID. The previous SID is added to the sIDHistory property.

a-signaturealgorithms.Description: This attribute indicates the type of algorithm that must be used to decode a digital signature during the authentication process.

a-siteguid.Description: The unique identifier for a site.

a-sitelinklist.Description: List of site links that are associated with this bridge.

a-sitelist.Description: List of sites connected to this link object.

a-siteobject.Description: The distinguished name for the site to which this subnet belongs.

a-siteobjectbl.Description: The list of distinguished names for subnets that belong to this site.

a-siteserver.Description: Licensing main server for a given Site.

a-sn.Description: This attribute contains the family or last name for a user.

a-spnmappings.Description: This multiple-valued attribute contains a list of service principal names (SPN) to show the equivalence of SPN types. The SPN is the name a client uses to uniquely identify an instance of a service. If you install multiple instances of a service on computers throughout a forest, each instance must have its own SPN. A given service instance can have multiple SPNs if there are multiple names that clients might use for authentication. For example, "ldap/..." SPNs could be mapped so that they are equivalent to "host/..." SPNs.

a-st.Description: The name of a user's state or province.

a-structuralobjectclass.Description: This constructed attribute stores a list of classes contained in a class hierarchy, including abstract classes. This list does contain dynamically linked auxiliary classes.

a-subclassof.Description: The parent class of a class.

a-subrefs.Description: List of subordinate references of a Naming Context.

a-subschemasubentry.Description: The distinguished name for the location of the subschema object where a class or attribute is defined.

a-superiordnsroot.Description: This is a system attribute that is used for referrals generation.

a-superscopedescription.Description: This attribute provides a description for a superscope.

a-superscopes.Description: This attribute is used to group together all the different scopes used in the DHCP class into a single entity.

a-supplementalcredentials.Description: Stored credentials for use in authenticating. The encrypted version of the user's password. This attribute is neither readable nor writable.

a-supportedapplicationcontext.Description: Specifies the object identifiers of application contexts that an OSI application supports.

a-syncattributes.Description: Attributes that contain information on the sync objects.

a-syncmembership.Description: List of members contained in a SAM builtin group for synchronization.

a-syncwithobject.Description: Distinguished name of the object being synchronized for the SAM builtin group/local policy synchronization.

a-syncwithsid.Description: For the SAM builtin group object/ local policy synchronization, this is the local group to which an object corresponds.

a-systemauxiliaryclass.Description: A list of auxiliary classes that cannot be modified by the user.

a-systemflags.Description: An integer value that contains flags that define additional properties of the class. See Remarks.

a-systemmaycontain.Description: The list of optional attributes for a class. The list of attributes can only be modified by the system.

a-systemmustcontain.Description: The list of mandatory attributes for a class. These attributes must be specified when an instance of the class is created. The list of attributes can only be modified by the system.

a-systemonly.Description: A Boolean value that specifies whether only Active Directory can modify the class. System-only classes can only be created or deleted by the Directory System Agent.

a-systemposssuperiors.Description: The list of classes that can contain this class. This list can only be modified by the system.

a-teletexterminalidentifier.Description: Specifies the Teletex terminal identifier and, optionally, parameters, for a teletex terminal associated with an object.

a-telexnumber.Description: A list of alternate telex numbers.

a-templateroots.Description: This attribute is used on the Exchange config container to indicate where the template containers are stored. This information is used by the Active Directory MAPI provider.

a-templateroots2.Description: This attribute is used on the Exchange config container to indicate where the template containers are stored. This information is used by the Active Directory MAPI provider

a-terminalserver.Description: Opaque data used by the Windows NT terminal server.

a-textencodedoraddress.Description: This attribute is used to support X.400 addresses in a text format.

a-thumbnaillogo.Description: BLOB that contains a logo for this object.

a-thumbnailphoto.Description: An image of the user. A space-efficient format like JPEG or GIF is recommended.

a-timerefresh.Description: This attribute has the interval during which a resource record that is contained in an Active Directory integrated zone should be refreshed for the DNS server. The default interval is 7 days.

a-timevolchange.Description: This attribute indicates the last time that a file in the remote storage volume was changed.

a-title.Description: Contains the user's job title. This property is commonly used to indicate the formal job title, such as Senior Programmer, rather than occupational class, such as programmer. It is not typically used for suffix titles such as Esq. or DDS.

a-tokengroups.Description: A computed attribute that contains the list of SIDs due to a transitive group membership expansion operation on a given user or computer. Token Groups cannot be retrieved if no Global Catalog is present to retrieve the transitive reverse memberships.

a-tokengroupsnogcacceptable.Description: This attribute contains the list of SIDs due to a transitive group membership expansion operation on a given user or computer. Token groups cannot be retrieved if a Global Catalog is not present to retrieve the transitive reverse memberships.

a-tombstonelifetime.Description: The number of days before a deleted object is removed from the directory services. This assists in removing objects from replicated servers and preventing restores from reintroducing a deleted object. This value is in the Directory Service object in the configuration NIC.

a-transportaddressattribute.Description: The name of the address type for the transport.

a-transportdllname.Description: The name of the DLL that will manage a transport.

a-transporttype.Description: The distinguished name for a type of transport being used to connect sites together. This value can point to an IP or SMTP transport.

a-treatasleaf.Description: Display-specifiers with this flag set to TRUE force the related class to be displayed as a leaf class even if it has children.

a-treename.Description: DNS name of the domain at the root of a tree.

a-trustattributes.Description: This attribute stores the trust attributes for a trusted domain. Possible attribute values are as follows:

a-trustauthincoming.Description: Authentication information for the incoming portion of a trust.

a-trustauthoutgoing.Description: Authentication information for the outgoing portion of a trust.

a-trustparent.Description: The parent in KERBEROS trust hierarchy.

a-trustpartner.Description: The name of the domain with which a trust exists.

a-trustposixoffset.Description: The Portable Operating System Interface (POSIX) offset for the trusted domain.

a-trusttype.Description: The type of trust, for example, Windows NT or MIT.

a-uascompat.Description: Indicates if the security account manager will enforce data sizes to make Active Directory compatible with the LanManager User Account System (UAS). If this value is 0, no limits are enforced. If this value is 1, the following limits are enforced.

a-uidnumber.Description: Contains an integer that uniquely identifies a user in an administrative domain.

a-uncname.Description: The universal naming convention name for shared volumes and printers.

a-unicodepwd.Description: The password of the user in Windows NT one-way format (OWF). Windows 2000 uses the Windows NT OWF. This property is used only by the operating system. Note that you cannot derive the clear password back from the OWF form of the password.

a-uniqueidentifier.Description: The uniqueIdentifier attribute type specifies a "unique identifier" for an object represented in the Directory.

a-uniquemember.Description: The distinguished name for the member of a group. Used by groupOfUniqueNames.

a-unixhomedirectory.Description: Contains the absolute path to the home directory.

a-unixuserpassword.Description: Contains a user password that is compatible with a UNIX system.

a-unstructuredaddress.Description: The IP address of the router (for example: 100.11.22.33).

a-unstructuredname.Description: The DNS name of the router (for example: router1.fabrikam.com).

a-upgradeproductcode.Description: This attribute contains the product code of other packages, such as applications, that can be upgraded by this package, or that can upgrade this package.

a-upnsuffixes.Description: The list of User-Principal-Name suffixes for a domain.

a-useraccountcontrol.Description: Flags that control the behavior of the user account.

a-usercertificate.Description: Contains the DER-encoded X.509v3 certificates issued to the user. Note that this property contains the public key certificates issued to this user by Microsoft Certificate Service.

a-userclass.Description: The userClass attribute type specifies a category of computer user.

a-userparameters.Description: Parameters of the user. Points to a Unicode string that is set aside for use by applications. This string can be a null string, or it can have any number of characters before the terminating null character. Microsoft products use this member to store user data specific to the individual program.

a-userpassword.Description: The user's password in UTF-8 format. This is a write-only attribute.

a-userpkcs12.Description: PKCS #12 PFX PDU for exchange of personal identity information.

a-userprincipalname.Description: This attribute contains the UPN that is an Internet-style login name for a user based on the Internet standard RFC 822. The UPN is shorter than the distinguished name and easier to remember. By convention, this should map to the user email name. The value set for this attribute is equal to the length of the user's ID and the domain name. For more information about this attribute, see User Naming Attributes.

a-usersharedfolder.Description: Specifies a UNC path to the user's shared documents folder. The path must be a network UNC path of the form **\\Server\Share\**Directory. This value can be a null string.

a-usersharedfolderother.Description: Specifies a UNC path to the user's additional shared documents folder. The path must be a network UNC path of the form **\\Server\Share\**Directory. This value can be a null string.

a-usersmimecertificate.Description: Certificate distribution object or tagged certificates.

a-userworkstations.Description: Contains the NetBIOS or DNS names of the computers running Windows NT Workstation or Windows 2000 Professional from which the user can log on. Each NetBIOS name is separated by a comma. Multiple names should be separated by commas.

a-usnchanged.Description: The update sequence number (USN) assigned by the local directory for the latest change, including creation. See also , USN-Created.

a-usncreated.Description: The update sequence number (USN) assigned at object creation. See also, USN-Changed.

a-usndsalastobjremoved.Description: Contains the update sequence number (USN) for the last system object that was removed from a server.

a-usnintersite.Description: The update sequence number (USN) for inter-site replication.

a-usnlastobjrem.Description: Contains the update sequence number (USN) for the last non-system object that was removed from a server.

a-usnsource.Description: Value of the USN-Changed attribute of the object from the remote directory that replicated the change to the local server.

a-validaccesses.Description: The type of access that is permitted with an extended right.

a-vendor.Description: This attribute identifies the vendor for an application.

a-versionnumberhi.Description: A general purpose major version number.

a-versionnumberlo.Description: A general purpose minor version number.

a-voltableguid.Description: The unique identifier for a Link-Track-Volume table entry.

a-voltableidxguid.Description: The index identifier for a Link-Track-Volume table entry.

a-volumecount.Description: The tracked volume quota for a given computer.

a-wbempath.Description: References to objects in other ADSI namespaces.

a-wellknownobjects.Description: This attribute contains a list of well-known object containers by GUID and distinguished name. The well-known objects are system containers. This information is used to retrieve an object after it has been moved by using just the GUID and the domain name. Whenever the object is moved, the system automatically updates the Distinguished Name portion of the Well-Known-Objects values that referred to the object. The file Ntdsapi.h contains the following definitions, which can be used to retrieve an object (the GUIDs that are associated to these objects are contained in Ntdsapi.h):

a-whenchanged.Description: The date when this object was last changed. This value is not replicated and exists in the global catalog.

a-whencreated.Description: The date when this object was created. This value is replicated and is in the global catalog.

a-wwwhomepage.Description: A web page that is the primary landing page of a website.

a-x121address.Description: The X.121 address for an object.

a-x500uniqueidentifier.Description: Used to distinguish between objects when a distinguished name has been reused. This is a different attribute type from both the uid and uniqueIdentifier types.
